svg.desc:
#direction: top
[Control|Represents the base class for user interface (UI) elements that use a ControlTemplate to define their appearance.]
[ContentControl|Represents a control with a single piece of content of any type.]
[Frame|Frame is a content control that supports navigation.]
[Hyperlink|An inline-level flow content element that provides facilities for hosting hyperlinks within flow content.]
[Span|Groups other Inline flow content elements]
[Inline|An abstract class that provides a base for all inline flow content elements.]
[TextElement|An abstract class used as the base class for the abstract Block and Inline classes.]
[FrameworkContentElement|FrameworkContentElement is the WPF framework-level implementation and expansion of the ContentElement base class. FrameworkContentElement adds support for additional input APIs (including tooltips and context menus), storyboards, data context for data binding, styles support, and logical tree helper APIs.]
[ContentElement|Provides a WPF core-level base class for content elements. Content elements are designed for flow-style presentation, using an intuitive markup-oriented layout model and a deliberately simple object model.]
[Page|Encapsulates a page of content that can be navigated to and hosted by Windows Internet Explorer, NavigationWindow, and Frame.]
[Window|Provides the ability to create, configure, show, and manage the lifetime of windows and dialog boxes.]
[NavigationWindow|Represents a window that supports content navigation.]
[ItemsControl|Represents a control that can be used to present a collection of items.]
[Selector|Represents a control that allows a user to select items from among its child elements.]
[TabControl|Represents a control that contains multiple items that share the same space on the screen.]
[FrameworkElement] <:- [Control] <:- [ContentControl] <:- [Frame] [ContentControl] <:- [Window] <:-[NavigationWindow] [FrameworkElement] <:- [Page]
[Control] <:- [ItemsControl] <:- [Selector] <:- [TabControl] [DependencyObject] <:- [ContentElement] <:- [FrameworkContentElement] <:- [TextElement] <:- [Inline] <:- [Span] <:- [Hyperlink]
